The main scoreboard live game is now fonctional and I added the first README file

Clarify that install script must be made executable

Specify that the Lite (non-GUI) version of Raspbian is preferred

This is recommended by the rpi-rgb-led-matrix library: https://github.com/hzeller/rpi-rgb-led-matrix/#all-raspberry-pi-versions-supported

Removes a documentation error that asked you to install the rpi-rgb-led-matrix library a second time

This was already installed via `install.sh` and doesn't need to be installed a second time.
